Polymetal Jumps First Day in Four as Gold and Silver Advance

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-27T15:55:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/polymetal-jumps-first-day-in-four-as-gold-and-silver-advance.html
OAO Polymetal, the Russian silver
and gold producer, gained for the first day in four as both
metals advanced.  Its shares rose as much as 6.6 percent before closing 2.1
higher at 549.5 rubles at the close in Moscow, helping to pare a
three-day, 13 percent slump.  Immediate-delivery gold gained as much as $76.05, or 4.8
percent, to $1,676.97 an ounce in  London . Silver advanced,
snapping a three-day losing streak.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
 jcorcoran13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  